category: FIRE Z
category comment: 

clue: Chisel the Z from an abundant mineral & it becomes this liquid measure equal to one-fourth of a gallon

response: a quart (from quartz)

clue: Take Z beer away from a word for a heavy drinker & get this person at a sporting event voicing their displeasure

response: booer (from boozer)

clue: Pop the Z off a pimple & get this Stephen King title

response: It (from zit)

clue: Deny the Z of a ballroom dance & it becomes this first name of a 19th century U.S. poet

response: Walt (from waltz)

clue: Take the Z off the case in a type of mystery novel with little violence & it becomes this word for shy

response: coy (from cozy)

